list_page_teaser: The law enforcement team on Twin Peaks is diverse, and they work well together.  Click to learn more!
description_html:
The law enforcement team on Twin Peaks is diverse. Agent Cooper and Sheriff Truman in particular may look at the world differently, but they share a preference for logic over emotion.

The team also works well together, with very little conflict. The images show that Lucy can be just as much of a boss as Harry is, and it is natural for Hawk and Andy to cooperate with them.

image_list.title: Dale Cooper
image_list.subtitle_html: Special Agent for the FBI
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Agent Cooper's spiritual portrait shows he is logical and highly intuitive.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Blue in this spiritual portrait represents Agent Cooper's dominant personality trait, his openness to new ideas.  In Extraverts, the dominant trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long vertical line to represent this, because it is the side of their personality that is most evident.
image_list.explain_aux: The Green in this spiritual portrait represents Agent Cooper's auxiliary personality trait, his fairly slight preference for reason over empathy.  In Extraverts, the auxiliary trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a horizontal line to represent this.

image_list.title: Harry S. Truman
image_list.subtitle_html: Sheriff of the Twin Peaks Sheriffs Department

In Extraverts, the dominant trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long vertical line to represent this, because it is the side of their personality that is most evident.
image_list.explain_aux: The Yellow in this spiritual portrait represents Sheriff Truman's auxiliary personality trait, his pragmatism.  In Extraverts, the auxiliary trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a horizontal line to represent this.

image_list.subtitle_html: Deputy Sheriff in the Twin Peaks Sheriffs Department

image_list.title: Tommy 'Hawk' Hill
image_list.subtitle_html: Deputy Sheriff in the Twin Peaks Sheriffs Department
image_list.gallery_page_teaser: Hawk's spiritual portrait shows he is intuitive and logical, much like Agent Cooper, but not as outgoing.  Click on the image to learn more!
image_list.explain_dom: The Green in this spiritual portrait represents Hawk's dominant personality trait, his objectivity and cool-headedness.  In Introverts, the dominant trait is directed inwardly, and spiritual portraits use a long horizontal line to represent this.
image_list.explain_aux: The Blue in this spiritual portrait represents Hawk's auxiliary personality trait, his openness to ideas.  In Introverts, the auxiliary trait is directed outwardly, and spiritual portraits use a vertical line to represent this, because it is more evident than the dominant function.
